The food here is REAL AUTHENTIC NIGERIAN FOOD! Delicious and addictive. You wont be able to move after you eat. The Igban were delicious,  I would of preferred with okra or bitter leaf instead of red peppers but the snails were delicious. These large snails are very hard to find anywhere, so enjoy your treasure.  The okra with mixed meat such as tripe and cows feet was delicious and perfectly spicy with that unique flavor. The bitter leaf was FANTASTIC and my favorite dish. Do you know how Powerful bitter leaf is? Bitterleaf is a super food and if you are feeling under the weather or near death it will being you back to life. Bitterleaf soup is life!!! The JALLOF rice Here is the REAL deal. The flavor is smoky and the rice was fresh and delicious. The pounded yam I enjoyed with my meals was fresh and delicious. If you want REAL AFRICAN FOOD COME HERE!!!! Great experience.

It was a disgraceful experience. I took a co-worker who had never had Nigerian food to this restaurant based on my Google search of restaurants in the area. As soon as I walked in, I observed the atmosphere to be dingy. That should have been my hint to walk right out. Nevertheless,  we stayed because my colleague was eager to try Nigerian food. It took almost 15 minutes for the attendant to take our order and when my guest who doesn't understand Nigerian food was trying to decide what to order, she appeared very impatient. She did apologize in advance that it would take a while since she has to fulfill a large take away order so we knew we would wait a while before the food arrived. When the food finally came, the white rice I ordered was brown and smelt like it was cooked a week ago. It also looked like it had been reheated several times. I immediately called and asked for it to be swapped for jollof rice. Needless to say, there was nothing memorable about the jollof rice. I used the stew that was supposed to be used with my white rice to eat the jollof rice. Again, this wasn't fresh at all. I cut into the cow leg only to hit a cold spot because it was not properly microwaved. I can't believe I paid $16 for a meal and service that was totally unsatisfactory. I had to apologize to my colleague because I may have totally destroyed her appetite for Nigerian food. It is rather unfortunate that this business does not appear to show respect for its customers based on the service and quality of food it served yesterday. This was my experience and I have no plan to return neither will I recommend this business .
